agreements datacube documentation

Source: R/manytreaties-agreements.R
agreements.Rd

The manytreaties::agreements datacube is a list containing 9 datasets: IEADB, HEIDI, TFDD, TREND, LABPTA, TOTA, GPTAD, GGO, and DESTA. Development of this datacube continues, so please let us know if you have any comments or suggestions.

agreements

Format

IEADB:

A dataset with 3,583 observations and 22 variables: treatyID, Title, Begin, End, Signature, Force, Term, Grounds, TypeAmbit, TypeAgree, TypeSubject, Lineage, Location, Auspices, Secretariat, TitleAlt, TextURL, Language, ..., Version, and mitchID.

HEIDI:

A dataset with 2,280 observations and 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Lineage, and heidiID.

DESTA:

A dataset with 987 observations and 11 variables: treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, TypeAgree, TypeAmbit, TypeGeo, TitleAlt, Language, and destaID.

TFDD:

A dataset with 953 observations and 35 variables: treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, TypeAgree, TypeAmbit, TypeRegion, TypeGeo, TypeSubject, Location, Secretariat, Comments, Source, tfddID, Infrastructure, Hydropower, Irrigation, Groundwater, ..., People_Interests, and AmendMech.

TREND:

A dataset with 710 observations and 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, and trendID.

LABPTA:

A dataset with 483 observations and 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, and labptaID.

TOTA:

A dataset with 442 observations and 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, and totaID.

GPTAD:

A dataset with 340 observations and 10 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, AgreementType, DocType, GeogArea, Signature, Force, and gptadID.

GGO :

A dataset with 4,532 observations and 26 variables: treatyID, Title, Begin, End, Signature, Force, Term, Grounds, TypeDomain, TypeAgree, TypeAmbit, TypeGeo, TypeSubject, Location, Depository, Published, Secretariat, Website, ..., Comments, and Source.

For more information and references to each of the datasets used, please use the manydata::call_sources() and manydata::compare_dimensions() functions.

Source

  • Mitchell, Ron B. et al. 2020. 'What we know (and could know) about international environmental agreements'. Global Environmental Politics 20.1, pp. 103-121.

  • Morin, Jean-Frederic, and Chantal Blouin. 2019. 'How environmental treaties contribute to global health governance'. Globalization and health 15.1, pp. 1-8.

  • Duer, Andreas, Leonardo Baccini, and Manfred Elsig. 2014. 'The Design of International Trade Agreements: Introducing a New Database'. The Review of International Organizations 9.3, pp. 353-375.

  • Oregon College of Earth and Oregon State University Atmospheric Science. 2021. Product of the Transboundary Freshwater Dispute Database.

  • Morin, Jean-Frederic, Andreas Duer, and Lisa Lechner. 2018. 'Mapping the trade and environment nexus: Insights from a new dataset'. Global Environmental Politics 18.1, pp. 122-139.

  • Raess, Damien, Andreas Duer, and D. Sari. 2018. 'Protecting labor rights in preferential trade agreements: The role of trade unions, left governments, and skilled labor'. The Review of International Organizations 2.13, pp. 143-162.

  • Alschner, Wolfgang, Julia Seiermann, and Dmitriy Skougarevskiy. 2017. 'Text-as-data analysis of preferential trade agreements: Mapping the PTA landscape'. UNCTAD Research Paper No. 5.

  • World Bank Group. 2014. Global Preferential Trade Agreement Database (GPTAD). Online database. World Bank Group.

  • Hollway, James, and Jael Tan. 'Global governance observations on international agreements' (2025).
